Weighing 8{ pounds and standing 13{ inches tall, Oscar was created by Metro-Goldwyn-Mayer studios art director Cedric Gibbons, who went on to win 11 of the trophies. The Academy holds all the rights on the statue and reserves the right to buy back an Oscar before someone takes it to a pawn shop, said Academy spokesman Bob Werden. Ben-Hur in 1959 was the most-awarded film with 11, and Walt Disney was the most-awarded person with 32. The motion picture industry's most coveted award, Oscar, was created 60 years ago and 1816 of the statuettes have been produced so far. 